a place for the gamelan orchestra to sit, as a village meeting point, host dance performances or simply be a place of rest for worshipers. this part of traditional balinese temple architecture has been copied by hotels all over the island and in the wider world. the open grass-roofed pavilions you see everywhere in bali are all derived from this original piece of temple design. to enter any temple you must be appropriately dressed with a sarong and sash. these are always available for rental at the large temples which attract a lot of tourists (usually included if you're paying 